'''Question 9
  Minimum Maximum'''
  
#Pseudo code

1. Reading number of test cases
2.for each test cases
3. reading number of values and reading and creating list 
4. calculating cost, cost will be minimum value of list*(length of list-1)
5. print cost
6. Goto next test case


#code




#Reading number of test cases
t = int(input())

while(t > 0):
    #decreasing test value by 1
    t -= 1 
    #reading number of input 
    n = int(input())
    #reading input values and creating list
    l = [int(x) for x in input().split()]
    #cost will be minimum value of list*(length of list-1)
    cost = min(l) *(len(l)-1)
    #print cost
    print(cost)
